#Q-4.12
  
  ##a-Classical Method
  print("Null Hypothesis : H0 >= 0.9, Alternate Hypothesis : H1 < 0.9, Tailness : Left Tail")
## [1] "Null Hypothesis : H0 >= 0.9, Alternate Hypothesis : H1 < 0.9, Tailness : Left Tail"
  n = 500
  x = 440
  a = 0.05 #As CI is not mentioned.
  po = 0.9
  pc = x/n
  Za = qnorm(a,0,1)
  Z = (pc - po) / sqrt((po*(1-po))/n)
  print("Since Z doesn't lies in Critical region , So H0 is accepted.")
## [1] "Since Z doesn't lies in Critical region , So H0 is accepted."
  ##b- p-value
  A = pnorm(Z,0,1)
  print("p-value > alpha , so H0 is accepted.")
## [1] "p-value > alpha , so H0 is accepted."
#Q-4.13
  
  ##a-Classical Method
  print("Null Hypothesis : H0 <= 0.75, Alternate Hypothesis : H1 < 0.75, Tailness : Right Tail")
## [1] "Null Hypothesis : H0 <= 0.75, Alternate Hypothesis : H1 < 0.75, Tailness : Right Tail"
  n = 200
  x = 75
  a = 0.05
  po = 0.75
  pc = x/n
  Za = qnorm(1-a,0,1)
  Z = (pc - po) / sqrt((po*(1-po))/n)
  print("Since Z doesn't lies in Critical region , So H0 is accepted.")
## [1] "Since Z doesn't lies in Critical region , So H0 is accepted."
  ##b- p-value
  A = pnorm(Z,0,1)
  pvalue = 1 - A
  print("p-value > alpha , so H0 is accepted.")
## [1] "p-value > alpha , so H0 is accepted."
#Q-4.14 
  
  ##a-Classical Method
  print("Null Hypothesis : H0 = 0.55, Alternate Hypothesis : H1 != 0.55, Tailness : Two Sided Tail")
## [1] "Null Hypothesis : H0 = 0.55, Alternate Hypothesis : H1 != 0.55, Tailness : Two Sided Tail"
  n = 150
  x = 785
  a = 0.10
  po = 0.55
  pc = x/n
  Za1 = qnorm(a/2,0,1)
  Za2 = qnorm(1-(a/2),0,1)
  Z = (pc - po) / sqrt((po*(1-po))/n)
  print("Since Z lies in Critical region , So H0 is Rejected and H1 is accepted.")
## [1] "Since Z lies in Critical region , So H0 is Rejected and H1 is accepted."
  ##b- p-value
  A = pnorm(Z,0,1)
  pvalue = 2 * A
  print("p-value > alpha , so H0 is accepted.")
## [1] "p-value > alpha , so H0 is accepted."
  ###Comment - Both methods contradicting.
  
#Q- 4.15
  
  print("Null Hypothesis : H0 = 46, Alternate Hypothesis : H1 != 46, Tailness : Two Sided Tail")
## [1] "Null Hypothesis : H0 = 46, Alternate Hypothesis : H1 != 46, Tailness : Two Sided Tail"
  mu = 46
  xbar = 46.18
  Sd = 0.5
  a = 0.01
  n = 25
  ta1 = qt(a/2,n-1)
  ta2 = qt(1-(a/2),n-1)
  t = (xbar - mu)/(Sd/sqrt(n))
  print("Since t value doesn't lies in critical region, so H0 is accepted.")
## [1] "Since t value doesn't lies in critical region, so H0 is accepted."

#Q-4.27
  
  print("Null Hypothesis : H0 <= 35, Alternate Hypothesis : H1 > 35, Tailness : Right Tail")
## [1] "Null Hypothesis : H0 <= 35, Alternate Hypothesis : H1 > 35, Tailness : Right Tail"
  n = 15
  Sdmu = 35
  
  ##a
  Sdx =37.4
  X2 = (n-1)*(Sdx^2)/(Sdmu^2)
  cat("Test Statistics : ", X2)
## Test Statistics :  15.98583
  ##b
  a = 0.01
  Xa = qchisq(1-a,n-1)
  cat("The region to the right side or greater than ", Xa , "is critical region.")
## The region to the right side or greater than  29.14124 is critical region.
  ##c
  ND = load.image("Q4.27c.jpg")
  plot(ND)

  ##d
  print("Since X value doesn't lies in critical region, so H0 is accepted.")
